data(starwars)
  1. create a graph showing the frequency of eye colors in the dataset.
ggplot(starwars, aes(eye_color))+
  geom_bar()

  1. Customize your graph to make it more presentable. Consider color, backgrounds, axes, etc.
ggplot(starwars, aes(eye_color))+
  geom_bar(fill = "seagreen", color = "black")+
  theme_classic()+
  xlab("Eye Color")+
  ylab("Frequency")+
  ggtitle("Starwars Character's Eye Color Frequency")

  1. Create a graph displaying information about characters height in each homeworld.
ggplot(starwars, aes(homeworld, height))+
  geom_boxplot()
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing non-finite outside the scale range
## (`stat_boxplot()`).

  1. Customize your graph to make it more presentable. Consider color, backgrounds, axes, etc.
ggplot(starwars, aes(homeworld, height))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 55, hjust = 1))+
  xlab("Homeworld")+
  ylab("Height")+
  ggtitle("Starwars Character's Height vs Homeworld")
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing non-finite outside the scale range
## (`stat_boxplot()`).

  1. Create a graph of characters height by mass.
ggplot(starwars, aes(mass, height))+
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

7.Customize your graph to make it more presentable. Consider color, backgrounds, axes, etc.

ggplot(starwars, aes(mass, height))+
  geom_point(color = "lightblue")+
  xlab("Mass")+
  ylab("Height")+
  theme_classic()+
  ggtitle("Starwars Character's Height by Mass")
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

  1. Add gender as a third variable to your graph of height by mass.
ggplot(starwars, aes(mass, height, color = gender))+
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

  1. Customize your graph to make it more presentable. Consider color, backgrounds, axes, etc.
ggplot(starwars, aes(mass, height, color = gender))+
  geom_point()+
  xlab("Mass")+
  ylab("Height")+
  scale_color_manual(name = "Gender", values = c("pink", "lightblue"))+
  ggtitle("Starwars Characters Mass and Height by Gender")+
  theme_classic()+
  facet_wrap(~gender)
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
